gui.tutorials.pythonBooleanLogic.typeCom:
Type the last block:

if (age > 18 and has_pass) or vip:
    print("Access allowed")
else:
    print("Access denied")

Parentheses group the check. Either the kid is over 18 AND has a pass, OR they are a VIP. Neither is true here, so Python prints "Access denied". Click Run to see all the decisions unfold.

gui.tutorials.pythonGuessTheNumber.elif:
Type the three-way check below, with blank lines between:

if guess == number:
    print("🎉 Correct!")

elif guess > number:
    print("📈 Too high")

else:
    print("📉 Too low")

elif is standard Python — short for "else if". Python checks each condition top to bottom and runs the first branch that's true. Notice == (two equals) for comparing — one equals means assignment, two equals means "is it the same?".
